In article <gradyCBGIu0.Bu6@netcom.com> grady@netcom.com (Grady Ward) writes:
>[...] use a hypbrid cipher system that uses DES in CBC mode
>output fed into a provably very-long-period additive indexed
>stream cipher (essentially a shift register cipher with a 
>very long period (say, >3000 bits)).


I assume you meant it the other way around.

I would take a provably long-period PRNG and feed that through DES-CBC
(or even multiple DES-CBC layers) to make sure there are no cycles
and the output is cryptographically strong.

